Tribal children from Kasaragod, Wayanad, Palakkad and Idukki will display their talents at the ongoing school arts festival on Saturday.According to an official release, children will present various tribal dance forms at the Gandhi Bhavan at 7 p.m. While 10 teams from various districts qualified to participate in the festival, the authorities have not included tribal arts as a competition item. In order to provide a platform for the students at the festival, the organisers have decided to organise their performance as a non-competition event. â€” Staff Reporter